title: Phil Anastasia's Pick 6
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports 
The host Renegades' Mike Welsh and the Chiefs' Evan Powell, the senior leaders of their respective teams, have been playing against each other since they were in third grade and representing Medford and Marlton. In a sense, they still are. Pick: Cherokee, 21-14. 
West Deptford at Collingswood: 
Coach Clyde Folsom is going for his 200th win with the visiting Eagles in his 25th season. Pick: West Deptford, 24-14. 
Winslow Township at Seneca: This is WJFL Constitution Division game matches two programs on the rise and two teams angling for mid-level seeds in their respective sectional tournaments. Pick: Winslow Township, 18-17. 
Highland at Camden Catholic: 
The host Irish are coming off a bye after stunning rival Camden with a fourth-quarter surge on Oct. 9. Pick: Camden Catholic, 33-19.
